{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/archimedes-and-the-integral-calculus-4cf875c6fee4", "time": 1683007995.853025, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/archimedes-and-the-integral-calculus-4cf875c6fee4/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Archimedes and the Integral Calculus | by Marco Tavora Ph.D. | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Archimedes and the Integral Calculus", "description": "Archimedes of Syracuse was the greatest scientist and mathematician of the classical antiquity. He was a polymath who contributed to a wide range of topics, including mathematics, physics, astronomy\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archimedes", "anchor_text": "Archimedes of Syracuse", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steven_Strogatz", "anchor_text": "Steven Strogatz", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://books.google.com.br/books?id=m1Q8AAAACAAJ&dq=Simmons+calculus&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_7vfjwrnpAhUFGbkGHaFAB5EQ6AEIKDAA", "anchor_text": "Simmons", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Quadrature_of_the_Parabola", "anchor_text": "The Quadrature of the Parabola", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isaac_Barrow", "anchor_text": "Barrow", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Descartes", "anchor_text": "Descartes", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre_de_Fermat", "anchor_text": "Fermat", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blaise_Pascal", "anchor_text": "Pascal", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Wallis", "anchor_text": "Wallis", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonaventura_Cavalieri", "anchor_text": "Cavalieri", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Gregory_%28astronomer_and_mathematician%29", "anchor_text": "Gregory", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isaac_Newton", "anchor_text": "Newton", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gottfried_Leibniz", "anchor_text": "Leibniz", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://books.google.com.br/books?id=m1Q8AAAACAAJ&dq=Simmons+calculus&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_7vfjwrnpAhUFGbkGHaFAB5EQ6AEIKDAA", "anchor_text": "Simmons", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Method_of_exhaustion", "anchor_text": "method of exhaustion", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://proofwiki.org/wiki/Quadrature_of_Parabola", "anchor_text": "this link", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_geometry", "anchor_text": "analytical geometry", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Descartes", "anchor_text": "Ren\u00e9 Descartes", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Method_of_exhaustion", "anchor_text": "method of exhaustion", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://github.com/marcotav", "anchor_text": "Github", "paragraph_index": 19}, {"url": "https://marcotavora.me/", "anchor_text": "www.marcotavora.me", "paragraph_index": 19}], "all_paragraphs": ["Archimedes of Syracuse was the greatest scientist and mathematician of the classical antiquity. He was a polymath who contributed to a wide range of topics, including mathematics, physics, astronomy, and engineering. Archimedes was also a brilliant inventor and weapons-designer.", "Some of his many achievements were:", "In the words of the mathematician Steven Strogatz, \u201c[t]o say [Archimedes] was ahead of his time would be putting it mildly\u201d.", "In this article, I will explain, based on Simmons, how he calculated the area inside a parabola segment (see Fig. 6 below). Archimedes\u2019 proof is contained in his treatise \u201cThe Quadrature of the Parabola\u201d written in the 3rd century BC (two thousand years before modern calculus was developed by several great mathematicians including Barrow, Descartes, Fermat, Pascal, Wallis, Cavalieri, Gregory, Newton, and Leibniz).", "In Figs. 6 and 7, the construction used by Archimedes to calculate the area S bounded by the chord AB is shown. He builds three triangles, namely \u0394ABC, \u0394ADC, and \u0394CEB, in the following way:", "Archimedes\u2019 goal was to show that the area S inside the parabolic segment is equal to 4/3 of the area of the triangle \u0394ABC:", "As we shall see in the last section, this can be done by first showing that", "and then applying the method of exhaustion mentioned above to the triangles underneath \u0394ACD and \u0394BCE and so on.", "In this section, I will show how to prove Eq. 2 (the proof follows Simmons). In the next one, I will prove, using a simple application of the method of exhaustion, that the area of the parabolic segment is equal to 4/3 of the area of the triangle \u0394ABC.", "The equation representing a parabola can be written as (with a convenient choice of axes):", "We then define three points A, B, and C and make the construction shown in Fig. 7 where:", "From Fig. 7, we find the following relation:", "According to Eq. 5, the vertical line that passes through C is a bisector of the chord AB. The point at which they cross is denoted by P. It is enough to prove that", "we automatically prove Eq. 2 (for more details see this link). From Fig. 7 we see that the vertical through E bisects the segment BC at point G and the segment BP at point H. If we now prove that:", "we directly obtain Eq. 6. Now the last step to prove Eq. 2 is to check that:", "To prove this we apply analytical geometry to Fig. 7. Naturally, Archimedes\u2019 proof was based on geometry only, since analytical geometry was only developed in the 17th century (by the French philosopher, mathematician, and scientist, Ren\u00e9 Descartes).", "After some simple algebra we obtain:", "Now using the method of exhaustion and re-applying the same procedure used with the chord ABC to the smaller triangles (below \u0394ACD and \u0394BCE), we obtain a geometric series whose sum gives us the result we were looking for:", "Thanks for reading and see you soon! As always, constructive criticism and feedback are always welcome!", "My Github and personal website www.marcotavora.me have some other interesting material both about mathematics and other topics such as physics, data science, and finance. Check them out!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Theoretical physicist, data scientist, and scientific writer."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F4cf875c6fee4&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Farchimedes-and-the-integral-calculus-4cf875c6fee4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Farchimedes-and-the-integral-calculus-4cf875c6fee4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Farchimedes-and-the-integral-calculus-4cf875c6fee4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_na